  "title": "PM cum BA (KYC/AML)",
  "description": "<p>Braindge Singapore Pte Ltd (Braindge) was founded in 2014 and is a company based in Singapore as the headquarter for Southeast Asia’s IT Solutions services. Braindge has a strong presence in both local and offshore banking industry which provides services in Project Management, Software Development, Risk Assessment, etc. </p><p><strong>Role Summary</strong></p><p>We seek a team of <strong>PM cum Business Analyst</strong> to support a large‑scale <strong>KYC/AML </strong>programme in a leading international bank. You will <strong>report to a Project Manager</strong> and <strong>operate closely with the PMO </strong>for<strong> </strong>governance, delivery tracking, reporting, and stakeholder coordination. </p><p>The BA owns requirements, process analysis, and UAT support, while contributing to PMO artefacts (plans, RAID, status reporting) for multi workstream delivery. </p><p>The proposed team will support:</p><ul><li>An ongoing implementation project </li><li>Other branch implementation project</li><li>Phase 2 of an existing initiative</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><strong>A. PMO & Delivery Support</strong></p><ul><li>Track milestones, dependencies, and critical path; <strong>proactively escalate</strong> risks/issues with impact/mitigation options.</li><li>Consolidate weekly status, KPIs, and executive dashboards for PM/PMO. </li></ul><p><strong>B. Stakeholder & Vendor Management</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate across <strong>Business, IT, Operations, Compliance</strong>, and external vendors; align priorities and      delivery expectations.</li></ul><p><strong>C. Business Analysis</strong></p><ul><li>Elicit, clarify, and document business and functional requirements; maintain <strong>requirements traceability</strong> from scope to UAT sign‑off.</li><li>Prepare UAT scope, entry/exit criteria, scenarios, and acceptance evidence, support defect triage through closure.</li><li>Produce BA deliverables (BRD/FRD, user stories, data mapping) to bank standards. </li></ul><p><strong>D. KYC/AML Domain Support</strong></p><ul><li>Apply <strong>CDD/EDD</strong>, risk assessment, suspicious activity themes, correspondent banking considerations, and regulatory expectations to ensure fit‑for‑purpose requirements and test coverage. </li></ul><p><strong>Must Have Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>5+ years</strong> in BA, PMO, or delivery roles in <strong>banking</strong> (regulatory/IT projects). </li><li>Hands‑on <strong>KYC/AML </strong>experience (processes, policies, or systems). </li><li>Strong analytical skills; excellent written & verbal communication. </li><li>Tool proficiency: <strong>Jira, Confluence, Zephyr (or equivalent), MS Project, Excel</strong> (advanced), PowerPoint.  </li></ul><p><strong>Good to Have</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with Japanese/global banks; prior PMO roles in large programmes.</li><li>Knowledge of change management and audit/compliance processes. </li></ul><p><strong>Personal Attributes</strong></p><ul><li>Structured, organised, delivery‑focused. </li><li>Resilient under changing priorities. </li><li>Ownership mindset. </li></ul><p><strong>Success Metrics (KPIs)</strong></p><ul><li>Timely, complete, and signed‑off requirements & UAT artefacts.</li><li>RAID and reporting quality (accuracy, timeliness, clarity) and stakeholder satisfaction.</li><li>On‑time delivery for assigned milestones with clear escalation/mitigation.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 6,
